definition[0]: if leaves, papers, clothes etc rustle, or if you rustle them, they make a noise as they rub against each other
example[0]: She moved nearer, her long silk skirt rustling around her.
example[1]: He rustled the papers on his desk.
definition[1]: to steal farm animals such as cattle, horses, or sheep
definition[2]: the noise made when something rustles
example[2]: the rustle of leaves in the wind
